pull_request.title: Module name error on deploy:hook when module name contains _deploy
pull_request.body:
Hello;

I noticed a rather specific error when the module's name contains the substring `_deploy` on its name.

Take `mymodule_deploy` as an example, with a `mymodule_deploy_deploy_myfunction` deploy hook and a `mymodule_deploy.deploy.php` file.

Running drush deploy:hook will fail with the following error:

```bash
[warning] Deploy hook function mymodule_deploy_deploy_myfunction not found in file mymodule.deploy.php
```

This is because `list($module, $name) = explode('_deploy_', $function, 2);` will set `$module` to just `mymodule` and not `mymodule_deploy` and, thus, the `$filename` will be wrong.

This is an uncommon but not rare scenario. In fact, it happened to me because I had a separate custom module dedicated to deploy hooks that had the `deploy` substring on the name.

The attached patch tries to solve this by first locating the deploy name and then substracting it from the function name in order to get the real module name.

issue.title: Deploy hook not found when module name contains _deploy
issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
This was originally reported in #5112 by @idiazroncero.

I noticed a rather specific error when the module's name contains the substring `_deploy` on its name.

Take `mymodule_deploy` as an example, with a `mymodule_deploy_deploy_myfunction` deploy hook and a `mymodule_deploy.deploy.php` file.

Running drush deploy:hook will fail with the following error:

```bash
[warning] Deploy hook function mymodule_deploy_deploy_myfunction not found in file mymodule.deploy.php
```

This is because `list($module, $name) = explode('_deploy_', $function, 2);` will set `$module` to just `mymodule` and not `mymodule_deploy` and, thus, the `$filename` will be wrong.

This is an uncommon but not rare scenario. In fact, it happened to me because I had a separate custom module dedicated to deploy hooks that had the `deploy` substring on the name.

**To Reproduce**
* Create a module named `myproject_deploy`.
* Create a `myproject_deploy.deploy.php` file which has a deploy function named `myproject_deploy_deploy_my_update()`.
* Run `drush deploy`

**Expected behavior**
Deploy hook is executed normally.

**Actual behavior**
```
 [warning] Deploy hook function myproject_deploy_deploy_my_update not found in file myproject.deploy.php
 [error]  Deploy hook failed: myproject_deploy_deploy_my_update
 [error]  Update aborted by: myproject_deploy_deploy_my_update
```

issue.title: DX-5153: Add support for custom Twig tests in the Twig validator.
issue.body:
Fixes #4579 **Testing steps** 1. Add the following code to an existing Twig template: ```twig
{{ myvar is instanceof('\\MyInterface') ? 'yes' : 'no' }}
``` 2. Run the Twig validation. This is expected to throw an error because the `instanceof` test is not part of core Twig: ```sh $ blt validate:twig ERROR in /app/docroot/themes/custom/mytheme/templates/mytemplate.html.twig >> Unknown "instanceof" test. ``` 3. Now edit `blt.yml` and add `instanceof` to the whitelisted Twig tests by adding the following section: ```yaml validate: twig: tests: - instanceof ``` 4. Run the validation again. Now there should not be any errors. ```sh $ blt validate:twig [OK] All 235 Twig files contain valid syntax. ```

pull_request.title: DX-5153: Add support for custom Twig tests in the Twig validator.
pull_request.body:
Fixes #4579 **Testing steps** 1. Add the following code to an existing Twig template: ```twig
{{ myvar is instanceof('\\MyInterface') ? 'yes' : 'no' }}
``` 2. Run the Twig validation. This is expected to throw an error because the `instanceof` test is not part of core Twig: ```sh $ blt validate:twig ERROR in /app/docroot/themes/custom/mytheme/templates/mytemplate.html.twig >> Unknown "instanceof" test. ``` 3. Now edit `blt.yml` and add `instanceof` to the whitelisted Twig tests by adding the following section: ```yaml validate: twig: tests: - instanceof ``` 4. Run the validation again. Now there should not be any errors. ```sh $ blt validate:twig [OK] All 235 Twig files contain valid syntax. ```

issue.title: Support custom Twig tests in `validate:twig`

labels.name: Enhancement
labels.description: A feature or feature request

issue.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
We can currently validate Twig files that contain custom [Twig functions](https://twig.symfony.com/doc/2.x/advanced.html#functions) and [Twig filters](https://twig.symfony.com/doc/2.x/advanced.html#filters), but when we validate templates that use custom [Twig tests](https://twig.symfony.com/doc/2.x/advanced.html#tests) an error is thrown:

```
  ERROR  in /app/docroot/themes/custom/mytheme/templates/mytemplate.html.twig (line 1)
  >>  1   <div>{{ content['#entity'] is instanceof('\\Drupal\\commerce_product\\Entity\\ProductInterface') ? content['#entity'].getDefaultVariation() : '' }}"
  >> Unknown "instanceof" test.
```

**Describe the solution you'd like**
Support custom Twig tests by whitelisting them in `blt.yml`, similar to how we support custom functions and filters:

```
validate:
  twig:
    functions:
      - my_custom_twig_function
    filters:
      - my_custom_twig_filter
    tests:
      - my_custom_twig_test
```

pull_request.title: Module name error on deploy:hook when module name contains _deploy
pull_request.body:
Hello;

I noticed a rather specific error when the module's name contains the substring `_deploy` on its name.

Take `mymodule_deploy` as an example, with a `mymodule_deploy_deploy_myfunction` deploy hook and a `mymodule_deploy.deploy.php` file.

Running drush deploy:hook will fail with the following error:

```bash
[warning] Deploy hook function mymodule_deploy_deploy_myfunction not found in file mymodule.deploy.php
```

This is because `list($module, $name) = explode('_deploy_', $function, 2);` will set `$module` to just `mymodule` and not `mymodule_deploy` and, thus, the `$filename` will be wrong.

This is an uncommon but not rare scenario. In fact, it happened to me because I had a separate custom module dedicated to deploy hooks that had the `deploy` substring on the name.

The attached patch tries to solve this by first locating the deploy name and then substracting it from the function name in order to get the real module name.

issue.title: Support custom Twig tests in `validate:twig`

labels.name: Enhancement
labels.description: A feature or feature request

issue.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
We can currently validate Twig files that contain custom [Twig functions](https://twig.symfony.com/doc/2.x/advanced.html#functions) and [Twig filters](https://twig.symfony.com/doc/2.x/advanced.html#filters), but when we validate templates that use custom [Twig tests](https://twig.symfony.com/doc/2.x/advanced.html#tests) an error is thrown:

```
  ERROR  in /app/docroot/themes/custom/mytheme/templates/mytemplate.html.twig (line 1)
  >>  1   <div>{{ content['#entity'] is instanceof('\\Drupal\\commerce_product\\Entity\\ProductInterface') ? content['#entity'].getDefaultVariation() : '' }}"
  >> Unknown "instanceof" test.
```

**Describe the solution you'd like**
Support custom Twig tests by whitelisting them in `blt.yml`, similar to how we support custom functions and filters:

```
validate:
  twig:
    functions:
      - my_custom_twig_function
    filters:
      - my_custom_twig_filter
    tests:
      - my_custom_twig_test
```

pull_request.title: Module name error on deploy:hook when module name contains _deploy
pull_request.body:
Hello;

I noticed a rather specific error when the module's name contains the substring `_deploy` on its name.

Take `mymodule_deploy` as an example, with a `mymodule_deploy_deploy_myfunction` deploy hook and a `mymodule_deploy.deploy.php` file.

Running drush deploy:hook will fail with the following error:

```bash
[warning] Deploy hook function mymodule_deploy_deploy_myfunction not found in file mymodule.deploy.php
```

This is because `list($module, $name) = explode('_deploy_', $function, 2);` will set `$module` to just `mymodule` and not `mymodule_deploy` and, thus, the `$filename` will be wrong.

This is an uncommon but not rare scenario. In fact, it happened to me because I had a separate custom module dedicated to deploy hooks that had the `deploy` substring on the name.

The attached patch tries to solve this by first locating the deploy name and then substracting it from the function name in order to get the real module name.

issue.title: Deploy hook not found when module name contains _deploy
issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
This was originally reported in #5112 by @idiazroncero.

I noticed a rather specific error when the module's name contains the substring `_deploy` on its name.

Take `mymodule_deploy` as an example, with a `mymodule_deploy_deploy_myfunction` deploy hook and a `mymodule_deploy.deploy.php` file.

Running drush deploy:hook will fail with the following error:

```bash
[warning] Deploy hook function mymodule_deploy_deploy_myfunction not found in file mymodule.deploy.php
```

This is because `list($module, $name) = explode('_deploy_', $function, 2);` will set `$module` to just `mymodule` and not `mymodule_deploy` and, thus, the `$filename` will be wrong.

This is an uncommon but not rare scenario. In fact, it happened to me because I had a separate custom module dedicated to deploy hooks that had the `deploy` substring on the name.

**To Reproduce**
* Create a module named `myproject_deploy`.
* Create a `myproject_deploy.deploy.php` file which has a deploy function named `myproject_deploy_deploy_my_update()`.
* Run `drush deploy`

**Expected behavior**
Deploy hook is executed normally.

**Actual behavior**
```
 [warning] Deploy hook function myproject_deploy_deploy_my_update not found in file myproject.deploy.php
 [error]  Deploy hook failed: myproject_deploy_deploy_my_update
 [error]  Update aborted by: myproject_deploy_deploy_my_update
```

issue.title: DX-5153: Add support for custom Twig tests in the Twig validator.
issue.body:
Fixes #4579 **Testing steps** 1. Add the following code to an existing Twig template: ```twig
{{ myvar is instanceof('\\MyInterface') ? 'yes' : 'no' }}
``` 2. Run the Twig validation. This is expected to throw an error because the `instanceof` test is not part of core Twig: ```sh $ blt validate:twig ERROR in /app/docroot/themes/custom/mytheme/templates/mytemplate.html.twig >> Unknown "instanceof" test. ``` 3. Now edit `blt.yml` and add `instanceof` to the whitelisted Twig tests by adding the following section: ```yaml validate: twig: tests: - instanceof ``` 4. Run the validation again. Now there should not be any errors. ```sh $ blt validate:twig [OK] All 235 Twig files contain valid syntax. ```

pull_request.title: DX-5153: Add support for custom Twig tests in the Twig validator.
pull_request.body:
Fixes #4579 **Testing steps** 1. Add the following code to an existing Twig template: ```twig
{{ myvar is instanceof('\\MyInterface') ? 'yes' : 'no' }}
``` 2. Run the Twig validation. This is expected to throw an error because the `instanceof` test is not part of core Twig: ```sh $ blt validate:twig ERROR in /app/docroot/themes/custom/mytheme/templates/mytemplate.html.twig >> Unknown "instanceof" test. ``` 3. Now edit `blt.yml` and add `instanceof` to the whitelisted Twig tests by adding the following section: ```yaml validate: twig: tests: - instanceof ``` 4. Run the validation again. Now there should not be any errors. ```sh $ blt validate:twig [OK] All 235 Twig files contain valid syntax. ```

issue.title: Support custom Twig tests in `validate:twig`

labels.name: Enhancement
labels.description: A feature or feature request

issue.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
We can currently validate Twig files that contain custom [Twig functions](https://twig.symfony.com/doc/2.x/advanced.html#functions) and [Twig filters](https://twig.symfony.com/doc/2.x/advanced.html#filters), but when we validate templates that use custom [Twig tests](https://twig.symfony.com/doc/2.x/advanced.html#tests) an error is thrown:

```
  ERROR  in /app/docroot/themes/custom/mytheme/templates/mytemplate.html.twig (line 1)
  >>  1   <div>{{ content['#entity'] is instanceof('\\Drupal\\commerce_product\\Entity\\ProductInterface') ? content['#entity'].getDefaultVariation() : '' }}"
  >> Unknown "instanceof" test.
```

**Describe the solution you'd like**
Support custom Twig tests by whitelisting them in `blt.yml`, similar to how we support custom functions and filters:

```
validate:
  twig:
    functions:
      - my_custom_twig_function
    filters:
      - my_custom_twig_filter
    tests:
      - my_custom_twig_test
```
